name: Jayhoun (Summer)
description:
Nature of Iran
The name of this ancient border of bygone Iran and Turan, everflowing in time, is now placed on a carpet that is called Jayhoun.
Jayhoun, which has historically been compared to Volga, completely freezes for four months during the year and countless passengers have fallen victim to its melting ice and freezing water. It houses a treasure trove of the most valuable works of art left from ancient Iran.
